Green methods include: Walking, Public Transit, Carpooling.

How the county leans politically based on the 2016 election results. Calculated by subtracting % voted democrat from % voted republican. Categorization as follows: 
<2% = Toss-up
>2% and <= 10% = Lean Republican/Democrat
>10% = Solid Republican/Democrat
Source: MIT Election Data and Science Lab, Harvard Dataverse
Comments: Alaska results are a statewide average, as they do report out retuls by their State House Districts, which cannot be rolled up into county-equivalent regions
